headline: Microsoft to invest $17.5B in India, PNC to allow bitcoin trading
summary: Market Catalysts host Julie Hyman tracks several of the day's top trending stock tickers, including Microsoft's (MSFT) plans to invest $17.5 billion in India over the next four years, Campbell's (CPB) reporting a decline in profit and revenue in its fiscal first quarter release, and PNC Financial Services Group (PNC) to allow bitcoin (BTC-USD) trading. headline: PNC Launches Bitcoin Trading With Coinbase for Wealthy Clients
summary: The move is the latest example of a traditional financial services provider offering digital asset trading through its own platform — a role still primarily filled by cryptocurrency exchanges such as Coinbase.  Through its partnership with PNC, Coinbase provides broker services and technology integration, facilitating trades of any amount of Bitcoin, according to Brett Tejpaul, co-CEO of Coinbase Institutional.
